{"type":"message","id":"62481fad","parentId":"f8e0e599","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:27:34.698Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gg233hdopo7s_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 152613\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- CFI Compression Experiment ✅ completed with key findings\r\n- Next pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nKey insights:\r\n1. CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals\r\n2. Constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap\r\n3. Three-dimensional compression filter needed: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\r\n4. Compression objective: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is to run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C). This would test:\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Compare against binary thresholds\r\n- Determine if this distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist related to this. The previous experiment was documented in `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`. I should create an experiment script that implements Strategy C.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pulse script and previous experiments, I need to:\r\n1. Create a new experiment script for Strategy C\r\n2. Run the experiment on 200 pulses with 80/20 split\r\n3. Compare results\r\n\r\nLet me create a script to run this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\n\r\nThe CFI Compression Experiment established that binary thresholds fail due to \"constant format\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1). The next step is to test the hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) which should distinguish metaprogramming artifacts from true research signals.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\n\r\nCreate the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment script (Strategy C) to test the combined formula against binary thresholds, building on the previous experiment's pulse data and methodology.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n# Date: 2026-03-24\r\n# Based on: CFI Compression Synthesis findings\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe hybrid formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Penalizes high-frequency constant tokens (freq=160 → min=1.0, no penalty)\r\n- Actually: this doesn't penalize them enough!\r\n\r\n## REVISED Formula\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × (1 - exp(-freq(T)/60))\r\n- freq=160 → factor = 0.93 (high CFI but multiplied by near-1)\r\n- freq=120 → factor = 0.86\r\n- freq=60 → factor = 0.63\r\n- freq=30 → factor = 0.39\r\n- freq=10 → factor = 0.15\r\n\r\n## Alternative: Score = CFI - λ/freq\r\n- λ = 20 (tuning parameter)\r\n- freq=160: score = CFI - 0.125 (CFI=1.0 → 0.875)\r\n- freq=120: score = CFI - 0.167 (CFI=0.96 → 0.793)\r\n- freq=60: score = CFI - 0.333 (CFI=0.5 → 0.167)\r\n- freq=30: score = CFI - 0.667 (CFI=0.5 → -0.167)\r\n\r\n## Decision\r\nUse: score(T) = CFI(T) - λ/freq(T) where λ = 15\r\n- \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00): score = 0.906\r\n- \"pulse\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00): score = 0.906\r\n- \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96): score = 0.850\r\n- \"ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON\" (freq=30, CFI=0.8): score = 0.533\r\n- True novelty (freq=3, CFI=0.5): score = 0.333\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n```\r\n\r\nfile: research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:26:29\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380454696}}
