{"type":"message","id":"6df227bd","parentId":"e1568546","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:27:43.166Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log file that was just created is `pulse_2026-03-24 152714.md`. But I also see in the log that there's a mutation `2026-03-24 152613.mutation` that got rejected (renamed to rejected). Let me read the new pulse log.","thinkingSignature":"0f50cbc73f1a6493e42682b7f1de98c8eee2bd38c43a83f1a7e9701c0dcffb64"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_et6tiflcsw5k_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 152714.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1966,"output":117,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14328,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774380460678}}
{"type":"message","id":"4367e0eb","parentId":"6df227bd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:27:43.171Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_et6tiflcsw5k_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 152714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. CFI Compression Experiment completed - found that CFI≥0.7 AND freq<120 is too aggressive\r\n3. Key insight: Constant Format Problem - tokens like \"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\" have freq=160, CFI=1.00 but are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n4. New insight: Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n5. Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring\r\n\r\nThe pending action is:\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThis is the most concrete next step. I should run this experiment to validate the hybrid scoring approach.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files I need:\r\n1. The pulse data - pulse_2026-03-24 152613.md or previous pulses\r\n2. I need to create a script or modify pulse.ps1 to run this experiment\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the recent pulse file mentioned: pulse_2026-03-24 152613.md, this is the latest pulse. I need to:\r\n1. Run the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment\r\n2. Document results\r\n\r\nLet me create the experiment. I'll need to:\r\n1. Parse the pulse log data\r\n2. Calculate scores for each token\r\n3. Compare with previous binary threshold results\r\n\r\nLooking at the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md file that was created, I should have access to the token data. Let me create a PowerShell script to run this experiment.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll focus on developing a targeted PowerShell script that implements the hybrid scoring approach. The core challenge is creating a flexible scoring mechanism that can distinguish between meaningful and non-meaningful tokens. I'll design the script to parse token data, apply the new scoring formula, and generate comparative metrics. This will involve carefully implementing the min(1, freq(T)/120) logic to create a nuanced scoring system that can differentiate between constant format and research trajectory tokens.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified the Constant Format Problem - tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts, not causal content. The proposed solution is hybrid scoring: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120). This experiment validates whether this formula distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\".\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and run the Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C) against 200 pulses, comparing against binary thresholds (CFI≥0.5 AND freq∈[3,120)) to validate the hybrid formula's effectiveness at filtering constant-format tokens while preserving research signals.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n1. DOWN-WEIGHT constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) → score≈1.0×1.0=1.0 (BUT capped at 1.0)\r\n2. PRESERVE research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → score varies by frequency\r\n3. ELIMINATE rare tokens (freq<3) → score=0 due to freq component\r\n\r\n**Key insight:** min(1, freq/120) means freq=160 caps at 1.0, not 1.33. So:\r\n- Constant-format (freq=160, CFI=1.0): score = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0\r\n- Research trajectory (freq=80, CFI=0.7): score = 0.7 × 0.67 = 0.47\r\n- Ratio: 0.47/1.0 = 0.47 (meaningful separation!)\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- **Pulses:** 200 (160 train, 40 test)\r\n- **Split:** 80/20\r\n- **Comparison:**\r\n  - Strategy A: freq(T) ≥ 3 (baseline)\r\n  - Strategy B: CFI(T) ≥ 0.5 AND freq(T) ∈ [3, 120) (binary threshold)\r\n  - Strategy C: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) ≥ 0.3 (hybrid scoring)\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n```\r\n$script = @'\r\nparam([int]`$n_pulses=200, [int]`$train_pct=80)\r\n\r\n$tokens = @{}\r\n$pulse_dir = \"pulse_logs\"\r\n$pattern = 'pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})'\r\n\r\n# Scan pulse logs\r\nGet-ChildItem \"$pulse_dir\" -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | ForEach-Object {\r\n    if (`$_.Name -match `$pattern) {\r\n        `$date = `$Matches[1]\r\n        `$content = Get-Content `$_.FullName -Raw\r\n        `$tokens[$_.Name] = @{\r\n            date = `$date\r\n            content = `$content\r\n            tokens = @{}\r\n        }\r\n   \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:27:34\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380463170}}
{"type":"message","id":"47fcdca9","parentId":"4367e0eb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:27:49.378Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the info. Let me write a concise summary of what happened in this pulse cycle.","thinkingSignature":"4ad358862a316eea649f29442e24a8570bcc81e73f489c1113d1caf3a2a46f85"},{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Sandbox Pulse 2026-03-24 152714 — Summary**\n\n**What happened:**\n1. **Previous mutation rejected** (pulse_2026-03-24 152613) — the Strategy C experiment draft was stored as a rejected mutation for reference\n2. **New pulse committed** (6 files changed, +197/-61 lines)\n3. **CFI Compression Synthesis** was the key finding: the constant-format tokens (`\"for next instantiation\"`, `\"pulse\"`, timestamps) all share freq=160, CFI=1.00 — they're **metaprogramming artifacts**, not causal content\n4. **Proposed solution:** Hybrid scoring formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` — the `min()` caps the frequency multiplier at 1.0, so constant-format tokens get a max score of 1.0 while lower-frequency research tokens score proportionally lower (e.g., freq=80, CFI=0.7 → score=0.47), creating meaningful separation\n\n**Next step queued:** Run the Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C) on 200 pulses to validate the formula against binary thresholds."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3344,"output":276,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15865,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774380463172}}
